Normalization¶

In [6]:
X_reshaped = X.values.reshape(-1,1)
y_reshaped = y.values.reshape(-1,1)
In [7]:
from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler
min_max_scaler = MinMaxScaler(feature_range = (0, 1))
X_scaled = min_max_scaler.fit_transform(X_reshaped)
y_scaled = min_max_scaler.fit_transform(y_reshaped)

Creating Training Set¶

Creates a dataframe with bitcoin prices since 50 days before a given day.

In [8]:
timesteps = 50
X_train = []
y_train = []
for i in range(timesteps, X_scaled.size):
    X_train.append(X_scaled[i-50:i, 0])
    y_train.append(X_scaled[i, 0])
X_train, y_train = np.array(X_train), np.array(y_train)

Creating Test Set¶

In [9]:
inputs = dataset[len(dataset) - len(y) - timesteps:].values
inputs = min_max_scaler.transform(inputs)
X_test = []
for i in range(timesteps, (y.size+timesteps)):
    X_test.append(inputs[i-timesteps:i, 0])
X_test = np.array(X_test)

y_test = np.array(y)

Linear Regression¶

Training the Linear Regression model on the Training set¶

In [10]:
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression

regressor = LinearRegression()
regressor.fit(X_train, y_train)
Out[10]:
LinearRegression()

Predicting the Test set results for Linear Regression¶

In [11]:
y_pred = regressor.predict(X_test)
y_pred = min_max_scaler.inverse_transform(y_pred.reshape(-1, 1))

Cross Validation Metrics for Linear Regression¶

In [12]:
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score
accuracies = cross_val_score(estimator=regressor, X=X_train, y=y_train, cv=10)
print("\nAccuracy of Cross Validation Method: {:.2f} %".format(accuracies.mean()*100))
print("Standard Deviation of Cross Validation Method: {:.2f} %".format(accuracies.std()*100))

Creating binary classification¶

If logReturn is less than 0 ------> 1¶
If logReturn is higher or equal than 0 ----> 0¶
In [15]:
diff = dataset_for_log["Diff"].to_numpy()[1:]
y_binary = (diff > 0) * 1 
y_binary
Out[15]:
array([1, 1, 1, ..., 1, 0, 0])
In [16]:
X_classification = []
y_classification = []
timesteps = 1
for i in range(len(diff) - timesteps):
    x_var = diff[i : i + timesteps]
    X_classification.append(x_var)
    y_var = y_binary[i + timesteps]
    y_classification.append(y_var)
In [17]:
X_classification = np.array(X_classification).reshape(-1, timesteps)
y_classification = np.array(y_classification)

Splitting dataset (80/20 ratio) and creating Training and Test set¶

In [18]:
split_size = int(dataset.shape[0]*0.8)
X_train_classification, y_train_classification = X_classification[:split_size], y_classification[:split_size]
X_test_classification, y_test_classification = X_classification[split_size:], y_classification[split_size:]

Training the Logistic Regression model on the Training set¶

Evaluation Metrics for Neural Network¶

In [31]:
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error,r2_score
import math

MSE = mean_squared_error(y_scaled, y_ann)
RMSE = math.sqrt(MSE) 
r2_score = r2_score(y_scaled, y_ann)

print(f"Mean Squared Error: {MSE} \nRoot Mean Squared Error: {RMSE} \nR2 Score: {r2_score*100}%")
